‘—ЩRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2019-09-13-twin0003.mdЩ@a16768a4ae306cc3411aa32491ac80bcfda1edd451028fb0d4ef26dac72845f1ІThis week in Nu #3‘ІThis week in Nu #3Ъ»Lots of stability improvements this week with better support for parsing, external commands, and more.
vsoch continues pushing Docker support forward, and added support for Ubuntu 18.04 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/663] #663
)
androbtech removed our dependency on regex, as part of the effort to improve build times (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/651] #651
)
max-sixty landed a CI guard to ensure the codebase was properly formatted (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/649] #649
)
wycats landed an improved parser that is both more stable and handles external commands better (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/632] #632
)
chhetripradeep added a 
``pwd``
 command (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/612] #612
)
tim77 added instructions for Fedora (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/607] #607
)
Lots of bugfixes by est31, tim77, pmeredit, vsoch, lesichkovm. Big thanks to bug reporters jeka, stephanemagnenat, twe4ked, rrichardson, bmurphy1976, joedborg, and lienke.
Fix for long-standing issue where externals freeze when outputting large amounts of output (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/664] #664
)
Added support for "did you mean?"-style errors when a column is mistyped. (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/662] #662
)
Added a lighter-weight table output format (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/631] #631
)
More plugins were made optional to help with build times. To get the full behavior be sure to build with 
``--all-features``
(
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/617] #617
)
Improved help system was added. Type 
``help``
 to get started (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/657] #657
)
Updates by ymgyt, androbtech, and pka to the 
[link: https://book.nushell.sh/] Nu book
Updates to the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/contributor-handbook] Contributor Handbook
, a guide for developers working on Nu
’ђђЪчTitle: This week in Nu #3
Path: This week in Nu #3
Content:
Lots of stability improvements this week with better support for parsing, external commands, and more.
vsoch continues pushing Docker support forward, and added support for Ubuntu 18.04 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/663] #663
)
androbtech removed our dependency on regex, as part of the effort to improve build times (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/651] #651
)
max-sixty landed a CI guard to ensure the codebase was properly formatted (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/649] #649
)
wycats landed an improved parser that is both more stable and handles external commands better (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/632] #632
)
chhetripradeep added a 
``pwd``
 command (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/612] #612
)
tim77 added instructions for Fedora (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/607] #607
)
Lots of bugfixes by est31, tim77, pmeredit, vsoch, lesichkovm. Big thanks to bug reporters jeka, stephanemagnenat, twe4ked, rrichardson, bmurphy1976, joedborg, and lienke.
Fix for long-standing issue where externals freeze when outputting large amounts of output (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/664] #664
)
Added support for "did you mean?"-style errors when a column is mistyped. (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/662] #662
)
Added a lighter-weight table output format (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/631] #631
)
More plugins were made optional to help with build times. To get the full behavior be sure to build with 
``--all-features``
(
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/617] #617
)
Improved help system was added. Type 
``help``
 to get started (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/657] #657
)
Updates by ymgyt, androbtech, and pka to the 
[link: https://book.nushell.sh/] Nu book
Updates to the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/contributor-handbook] Contributor Handbook
, a guide for developers working on Nu
